<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-261-656  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 261 656.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Learning  March 1990 v9 n6 p42(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New upgrade adds desktop publishing power. (Timeworks Inc's WordWriter 4) (Software Review) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Leonard, Jenelle.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Timeworks Inc.' Word Writer 4 offers Commodore 64 users extensiveword processing and desktop publishing capabilities for $39.95,with a money-back guarantee.andP;  Word Writer 4 retains the wordprocessing power of Word Writer 3 and adds graphics and layoutfeatures.andP;  The word processing aspect includes continuousformatting, automatic word wrapping, &quot;book marks,&quot; an 85,000 wordspelling dictionary, a 60,000 word thesaurus, search and replacecommands and an outlining option.andP;  For desktop publishing, WordWriter 4 provides eight fonts in 13 sizes and five &quot;specialeffects,&quot; a Mini-Graphic Library, two printing modes, textlayouts, macros, and text importing.andP;  The Quick-Start Mini Manualcombined with the help screens familiarizes the user with thebasics with just a few hours effort.andP;  Unfortunately, the user willneed to learn many keystrokes, using the two keyboard overlaysprovided.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Timeworks Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Word Writer 4 (Word processing software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationWord processing softwareDesktop publishing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>